body:
What jobs do you guys have and what are your responsibilities in that job?

Personally I am a cashier at a small sushi restaurant and I have to:
  • Take orders
  • Bag food items w/ utensils, soy sauce, napkins etc..
  • Make minor food items such as miso soup and shrimp tempura
  • Cleaning tables and the floor

replies.body:
Alright, least start from least hours to most?
  • Local library in town - shelving book returns, making space for more books, preparing crafts and activities for children's program
  • Local restaurant in town - working the front and back, as a host and a dishwasher / prep guy. It's mostly just washing dishes for 5+ hours straight
  • Canadian Tire - cashier, putting away returns, sometimes on the floor doing other stuff.
If you want to be technical, I guess the restaurant is the only "summer job", since it's the only one I picked up just for the summer.
